A '''sector fleet''' was a type of [[Navy|naval]] [[fleet]] formation that was used by the [[Galactic Republic]], and later the [[Galactic Empire]] and the nascent [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Imperial Era]].

==Republic Navy==
The [[Republic Navy|Galactic Republic Navy]] used local sector fleets during the [[Clone Wars]]. A [[Abrion sector fleet|sector fleet]] was active in the [[Abrion sector]],<ref name="Mustafar">{{EncyclopediaCite|Mustafar and Other Planets in the Outer Rim}}</ref> while another [[Ferra sector fleet|sector fleet]] was active in the [[Ferra sector]].<ref name="Friends">''[[Friends Like These]]''</ref>

==Imperial Navy==
[[File:Lothal-sector-fleet.png|thumb|right|250px|The Lothal sector fleet in orbit above Lothal.]]
A [[sector]] [[fleet]] in the [[Imperial Navy]] of the [[Galactic Empire]] was a type of [[Navy|naval]] fleet formation that,<ref name="Legacy" /> together with other [[Imperial Military]] and intelligence assets, formed a [[Sector Group]].<ref name="Dawn">''[[Dawn of Rebellion]]''</ref> Sector fleets were allocated to the 1,024 sectors of [[the galaxy]], and could be local naval forces,<ref name="Legacy" /> or could also be a major numbered fleet of the Imperial Navy.<ref name="Friends" /> The [[Lothal sector fleet]] was one such fleet that served as a small anti-[[Smuggler|smuggling]] [[task force]] under the command of [[Admiral]] [[Kassius Konstantine]], and blockaded the sector while it hunted insurgents.<ref name="Dawn">''[[Dawn of Rebellion]]''</ref> Its efforts were later considered inadequate by [[Governor]] [[Arihnda Pryce]], who requested that the Imperial [[Seventh Fleet (Galactic Empire)|Seventh Fleet]] reinforce the Empire in the sector.<ref name="Steps">''[[Star Wars Rebels: Steps Into Shadow]]''</ref> The [[Lothal sector]] fleet consisted of six [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyers]] including the [[flagship]] ''[[Relentless]]'',<ref name="Legacy" /> and two [[Arquitens-class command cruiser|''Arquitens''-class command cruisers]].<ref name="Forgotten">{{Rebels|The Forgotten Droid}}</ref>

The [[Adelhard's fleet|Anoat sector fleet]] was another local sector fleet that operated in the [[Anoat sector]] under the command of [[Governor]] [[Ubrik Adelhard]]. It consisted of a number of [[Imperial II-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial II''-class Star Destroyers]] including the flagship ''[[Dread Omen]]''. It later served as the naval forces of the [[Ubrik Adelhard's Imperial remnant|Imperial remnant]] of Governor Adelhard when the Empire splintered.<ref name="Uprising">''[[Star Wars: Uprising]]''</ref> Local sector fleets could operate outside of their assigned sectors while on certain missions.<ref name="Relics">{{Rebels|Relics of the Old Republic}}</ref> Additionally, the Imperial Navy maintained at least one major numbered sector fleet, the [[14th Sector Fleet]].<ref name="Friends" />

==The Alliance==
[[File:Home_Base_and_its_fleet.png|thumb|left|210px|The Phoenix Cell, an Alliance sector fleet]]
"The Alliance," the name given by Rebel leader [[Mon Mothma]] to the nascent [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]], utilized local rebel cells with naval forces as sector fleets. One such sector fleet was [[Phoenix Cell]], which operated in the Lothal sector and was led by [[Commander]] [[Jun Sato]]. The Phoenix Cell, at the time it was considered a sector fleet,<ref name="The Rebel Files">''[[Star Wars: The Rebel Files]]''</ref> consisted of the flagship [[Pelta-class frigate|''Pelta''-class frigate]] ''[[Phoenix Home]]'', five [[CR90 corvette]]s, and [[Phoenix Squadron]].<ref name="Siege of Lothal">''[[Star Wars Rebels: The Siege of Lothal]]''</ref> It participated on the [[action at Mustafar]]<ref name="Fire">{{Rebels|Fire Across the Galaxy}}</ref> in [[4 BBY]]<ref name="Date">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]'' dates the [[action at Mustafar]] to [[4 BBY]].</ref> to assist in rescuing the [[Spectres]] rebel cell from the Empire.<ref name="Fire" />

